headline: Teradyne stock plummeting after updating its guidance
summary: Teradyne (TER) stock dropped by as much as 17% ahead of Tuesday's session close after the automated test equipment (ATE) manufacturer revised its guidance lower. Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton report more on Teradayne's stock moves. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.

headline: Why Teradyne (TER) Shares Are Plunging Today
summary: Shares of semiconductor testing company Teradyne (NASDAQ:TER) fell 20.2% in the morning session after the company lowered its guidance ahead of its Investor Day event (2025). Teradyne guided for sales to be flat to down 10% (vs previous revenue growth expectations of between 5% and 10%). Management cited uncertainty from tariffs and trade restrictions.
